I've made this several times and it seems to turn out different each time - not sure why. For New Year's this year I used dried black eyed peas because the store was out of canned (high hopes for 2010?). Cooked them less than the package instructions and they still turned to mush. Okay for soup but I would use canned or frozen peas next time for the more reliable and firmer texture. I also used Rotel tomatoes as one reviewer suggested and they were disgusting. I prefer parsley over cilantro and one cup of vinagrette is usually more than enough. I would suggest tasting your balsamic vinegar first and maybe subbing with some red wine vinegar as I used a good aged balsamic and it was too sweet. That said, this is a good dish for a large gathering and the flavor improves remarkably as it stands. Make it at least a day ahead.

