Really good, healthy dip. I could not find canned black-eyed peas in my local store. I used frozen instead. The frozen required about 1 hour cooktime, but I just prepared everything else in the interim (BTW, the frozen I used were labeled purple-hull peas). I used Ken's Light Olive Oil Viniagrette, which was a great choice. I also cut the Tabasco to 1/3T and the jalapeno to 1/2 of a big one, since kids would also be eating. I added one cup frozen corn for color and sweetness and cut the peas to 3.5 cups. I did not marinate for 4 hours, since I had a difficult time finding the canned peas. I just tossed the warm, just-cooked peas into the dressing and stuck in the freezer for 30 minutes before leaving. Still tasted great!

